<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-10-14T01:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-10-14T01:35:00-05:00" n="588" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/39: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-14T10:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">October 14,
                                        1921—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 15—6:22
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. British Chargé d’Affaires has received instructions to reemphasize
                            protest referred to in the Legation’s 52, September 4th, and 59,
                            September 21st.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
